  "title": "Core Concepts of Key Concepts in Cybersecurity",
  "lessonText": "Understanding core cybersecurity concepts is essential for navigating the digital landscape.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• **Threat**: A potential cause of an unwanted incident in cybersecurity. \n• **Vulnerability**: A weakness in a system that can be exploited. \n• **Risk**: The potential for loss or damage when a threat exploits a vulnerability. \n• **Data Analyst's Role**: As discussed in the earlier lesson, understanding the expectation vs reality of a data analyst's life is crucial in recognizing how data security fits into their responsibilities. \n• **Interactive Coding Example**: Recall the function `def check(data):` which identifies if a system is at risk. \n• **Challenge Reminder**: Remember to fill in the blanks using terms from earlier lessons about cybersecurity concepts. \n• **Quiz Insight**: Reflect on the quiz question regarding potential causes of unwanted incidents as you explore these concepts further."
  }
